    <item>
      <title>Are you not Nature?</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/are-you-not-nature/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 04 Jul 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/are-you-not-nature/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;../../assets/images/wiapost/5192-Are-You-Not-Nature.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Are you not Nature?&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Are you not Nature? 
    &lt;div id=&#34;are-you-not-nature&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#are-you-not-nature&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If a man thinks he has done something against Mother Nature  &lt;br&gt;
that is why nature is punishing him or going to punish him then  &lt;br&gt;
he forgets that he himself is part of the parcel of nature.  &lt;br&gt;
There is no other separate nature away from your own bodily existence.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Biological Footprint of Human</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/biological-footprint-of-human/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 May 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/biological-footprint-of-human/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;../../assets/images/wiapost/5188-Biological-Footprint-Of-Human.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Biological Footprint of Human&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Biological Footprint of Human 
    &lt;div id=&#34;biological-footprint-of-human&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#biological-footprint-of-human&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Birds fly in the sky without footprint, &lt;br&gt;
Animals cannot walk on the earth without a footprint. &lt;br&gt;
Those who want to fly don&amp;rsquo;t create a nest to live but to rest. &lt;br&gt;
Those who want to walk create a den and die in those dens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Death happen to birds also &lt;br&gt;
But, their living noticed by everyone  &lt;br&gt;
and death known to none. &lt;br&gt;
Death happens to animal also &lt;br&gt;
They leave a rotten body behind  &lt;br&gt;
for other animals to eat.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
